This paper deals with voting rules, which is a topic in computational social choice (cs.GT). The use of approximations and the consideration of worst-case and average-case scenarios suggest a focus on algorithmic aspects, which are also relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of data sets suggests a possible connection to data science (cs.DS) and social informatics (cs.SI).
